        Retrieves the properties for rendering a single node. Additionally, the return value allows to control whether or not to omit this node from rendering. If false is returned, the node will not be rendered. Consequently, any modifications to the properties map will have no effect.

        The properties are stored in the Map argument. Note that if an implementation of a base class is overridden, it is probably a good idea to call super.getNodeProperties(node, properties); at the beginning of the method.
